## Loopback Address

The loopback address is a way you can use to ping yourself and to check if your IP configuration for your device is correct. In a way its like making sure that your ID card is actually working and is able to talk to other objects that have an ID card. You do that with the ping command like so:

```
ping 127.0.0.1
```

That address, 127.0.0.1, is always your own device. It never leaves your machine. Think of it purely as a self-check before you bother trying to talk to anyone else.

