## Reserved Addresses

A reserved address is a special kind of IP address. They are ID cards that only work within your own specific room. Now how is that valuable? Its valuable because of the fact that important objects in your room need to have an ID card that does not change. This is achieved through DHCP reservations, which we will cover shortly, where the butler is told by you that this specific ID card is going to stay with this specific object no matter what.

