## Virtual IP (VIP)

A VIP is a different kind of IP address and therefore a different kind of ID card. This kind of ID card acts more like a club badge. Rooms that are occupied by the same members who use that VIP ID card are registered as belonging to the same kind of club.

Now how would that be useful?

It is useful for security reasons. If a robber was targeting a specific room number he would find it easily. But if all of them shared the same club assignment instead he would be even more confused about which room to actually go after.

It also helps with network flexibility. This club badge would make sure the room that hosts it could be a different room if the original room was under maintenance or for some other reason.

That is also why it is highly available. If said room got burned down the club badge could just get transferred to another room entirely.

And it is important for load balancing. You have this club that has an assortment of rooms and they all need to receive the minutes of the club meeting evenly. Now the bearer of the club badge has separate magic powers like a load balancer that allows them to transmit all the paperwork evenly towards all of the club rooms. But here is the important thing to remember: the VIP is just the front door, it is just an address. The load balancer is the actual engine behind it doing the distribution. The VIP can help with distributing the paperwork but it is not necessarily the one with the magic powers.

